27/11/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The acting director of the BiH Federation Intelligence and Security Service, Zdravko Jukic, testified before a panel of the BiH Parliament on Wednesday (26 November) about recent allegations concerning leaked classified information.
Tihomir Gligoric, chairman of the parliamentary committee, said Jukic discussed possible violations of law by the intelligence services, as well as human rights restrictions.
Also Wednesday, the BiH Federation Interior Ministry denied press speculation about conflicting interests within the "special purpose" unit of the police.
"The special police unit is made up of professional and well-trained individuals who carry out the most complex tasks and thus safeguard the security of everyone in the Federation," read the ministry's press release.
(FENA, BBC - 26/11/03)
